## Create and view Businesses [/api/v2/auth/businesses]

### Create a New Business [POST]
You may create your own business using this action.
This action takes a JSON payload as part of the request.
Response then return specific header and body.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "business_name": "Fuego Entertainment",
            "description": "Record Label",
            "location": "Meru",
            "category": "Music"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "business_data": {
                    "business_id": 1,
                    "business_name": "Fuego Entertainment",
                    "category": "Music",
                    "description": "Record Label",
                    "location": "Meru"
                    "owner": "timmutai@email.com"
                "msg": "Business created successfully.",
            }

### Retrive all Businesses [GET]
You may view all your business using this action.
This action takes a JSON payload as part of the request.
Response then return specific header and body.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "all_businesses": [
                    {
                        "business_id": 1,
                        "business_name": "Fuego Entertainment",
                        "category ": "Music",
                        "description": "Record Label",
                        "location ": "Meru",
                        "owner": "timmutai@email.com"
                    }
                ]
            }


## Retrive, Update and Delete Businesses [/api/v2/auth/businesses/{business_id}]

+ Parameters
    + business_id (number) - ID of the Business in the form of an integer

### Update business by ID [PUT]

You may update your own business using this action.
This action takes a JSON payload as part of the request.
Response then return specific header and body.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "business_name": "Hasta La Entertainment",
            "description": "Record Label",
            "location": "California",
            "category": "Music"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "business_data": {
                    "business_id": 1,
                    "business_name": "Hasta La Entertainment",
                    "category": "Music",
                    "description": "Record Label",
                    "location": "California"
                    "owner": "timmutai@email.com"
                "msg": "Business updated successfully.",
            }
### Retrive business by ID [GET]
You may retrive one business by id using this action.
This action takes a JSON payload as part of the request.
Response then return specific header and body.


+ Response 200 (application/json)

            {
                "business_id": 1,
                "business_name": "Fuego Entertainment",
                "category ": "Music",
                "description": "Record Label",
                "location ": "Meru",
                "owner": "timmutai@email.com"
            }

### Delete business item [DELETE]
You may delete one business by id using this action.
This action takes a JSON payload as part of the request.
Response then return specific header and body.


+ Response 200 (application/json)

            {
                "msg": "The business has been deleted successfully."
            }

## Create and view Reviews [/api/v2/auth/businesses/{business_id}/reviews]

+ Parameters
    + business_id (number) - ID of the Business in the form of an integer

### Create a New Review [POST]
You may create your own reviews about a particular business using this action.
This action takes a JSON payload as part of the request.
Response then return specific header and body.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "review_name": "Fuegooo Music",
            "body": "They have the best music services in the business"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "msg": "Review added successfully."
                "review_data": {
                    "body": "They have the best music services in the business",
                    "business_id": 1,
                    "owner": "timmutai2@email.com",
                    "review_id": 1,
                    "review_name": "Fuegooo Music"
            }

### Retrive all Businesses [GET]
You may view all your business using this action.
This action takes a JSON payload as part of the request.
Response then return specific header and body.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "all_reviews": [
                    {
                        "body": "They have the best music services in the business",
                        "business_id": 1,
                        "owner": "timmutai2@email.com",
                        "review_id": 1,
                        "review_name": "Fuegooo Music"
                    }
                ]
            }